HEADWORD: Toaster
<hw>Toast"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
toasts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kitchen utensil for toasting bread, cheese,
etc.</def><-- since 1950, usu. operated by electricity, with heating
coils arranged so as to brown a slice of bread evenly over both
surfaces. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- <col><b>Toaster oven</b></col>. an electrical toaster. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toasting</ent>⟦br⟧
